ans, and students of Eastern Europe and the Middle East with a new understanding of the complexities and contradictions of modern Turkish experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aElite (Social sciences)xHistoryxTurkeyxBlack Sea Coast. 0aElite (Social sciences)zTurkeyzBlack Sea CoastxHistory. 0aIslam and politicsxHistoryxTurkeyxBlack Sea Coast. 0aIslam and politicszTurkeyzBlack Sea CoastxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aagha families.  aagriculture.  aamnesia.  aarmy.  abelief.  acoastal region.  aempire.  afaith.  afamily life.  afeudal system.  afeudalism.  aislam.  aislamic world.  aislamic.  amiddle east.  amiddle eastern.  amilitary.  amodern world.  amodernity.  anation state.  anew republic.  aold republic.  aottoman.  aprohibition.  aregional.  areligion.  areligious studies.  asocial justice.  asocial progress.  asoldiers.  aturkey.  aturkish.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092912840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520929128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520929128/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles